The paper deals with two fundamental problems in computational geometry and algorithm design: computing dominance product and solving the $L_\infty$ Closest Pair problem in high dimensions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
